I wasn't too impressed with the survey and would like to have seen one on a much larger scale. I do like the mention that a bunch EQ'ers play EQ with loved ones. To be honest, if I had not introduced Yai to EQ, I would have already cancled my accounts. Having her to play side by side with allowed me to enjoy EQ again. I personally don't like grouping with a lot of strangers, and she provided the group I needed to get out of my slump at 12th. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Then we took that extra step of joining MacLear and I found another whole new level to EQ.<br>
<br>
