<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <br>
Jeffryn watched the forest around Fironia Vie from the small bridge that led away from the outpost and listened to the sounds from the trees. Every now and then he would hear the distant growl of a drolvarg. He had met one in battle with a pilgrim and knew them to be ferocious and mean. He thought about what brought him here, to this remote place, so far away from his home in Surefall Glade. He sometimes questioned his desire for adventure and often thought of the reletively easy job he had as a messenger for Corun Finisc.<br>
<br>
His doubts would bring fear into his heart, like that he had felt his first time here when he had the ill luck of looking at a drachnid eye to eye. Even now he could feel, back in the recesses of his being, that fear and doubt. He tapped his sword, as if to reassure him that it was there, like his courage to face what was out there. He wondered if he could face them, if he could stand tall and prevail.<br>
<br>
He glanced over to Yaibong, sitting on a block talking to a barbarian lad about summoned daggers. The sun glistened off the tip of her staff that lay acrossed her lap as she giggled and gave him a glance back. A glance that said a thousand things in the silence that traveled between them.<br>
<br>
Yes, he knew, he could face those dangers. He was not alone out there, for there she was, brave beside him, and together their strength would carry them to victory time and again...<br>
